        output='# AI Segment Revenue Sub-Components Disclosed for FY2025\n\n## Top-Level Disaggregation (from the Revenue Table)\n\nThe AI segment total revenue of **$3,201 million** for FY2025 is disaggregated into two disclosed line items:\n\n| AI Sub-Component | FY2025 | FY2024 | FY2023 |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Advertising** | $1,844 | $1,728 | $2,323 |\n| **AI Solutions & Infrastructure** | $1,357 | $892 | $638 |\n| **AI (Total)** | $3,201 | $2,620 | $2,961 |\n\n## Qualitative Sub-Components of "AI Solutions & Infrastructure"\n\nThe notes describe three revenue streams within AI Solutions & Infrastructure, but **do not report separate dollar figures for each in the tables**:\n\n1. **Premium subscriptions on X and Grok** — recognized ratably over the subscription term (month-to-month up to one year)\n2. **Data licensing arrangements** — recognized ratably over the period (month-to-month up to two years)\n3. **API access to Grok models** — recognized ratably over the contract term (month-to-month up to one year) for stand-ready access, or as consumed for usage-based arrangements\n\n## Incremental Granularity from MD&A (YoY Change Disclosures Only)\n\nThe MD&A provides **change amounts** (not absolute balances) for FY2025 vs. FY2024:\n\n- Advertising revenue **increased $116 million**\n- AI Solutions & Infrastructure revenue **increased $465 million**, driven by:\n  - X and Grok subscription revenue: **+$365 million**\n  - Data licensing arrangements: **+$88 million**\n  - (API access change not separately quantified)\n\n## What Is NOT Disclosed with Revenue Granularity\n\n| Item Not Disclosed | Notes |\n|---|---|\n| **Absolute dollar values for subscriptions, data licensing, and API access separately** | Only the aggregate "AI Solutions & Infrastructure" figure appears in the table; MD&A gives only YoY deltas for two of the three |\n| **API access revenue** (absolute or change) | Mentioned qualitatively but never quantified, even as a YoY change |\n| **X subscriptions vs. Grok subscriptions split** | Always combined as "X and Grok subscription revenue" |\n| **Consumer vs. enterprise split within AI** | No customer-type revenue breakdown for the AI segment (unlike Connectivity, which splits Consumer vs. Enterprise & Government) |\n| **Advertising sub-categories** (e.g., display, video, sponsored) | No breakdown beyond the single "Advertising" line |\n| **Geographic revenue breakdown for AI** | Not provided |\n| **Principal vs. agent (gross vs. net) revenue split for advertising** | Policy is described (gross for direct X platform sales; net for SSP-partner sales), but no dollar split is disclosed |\n| **Products vs. services split within AI** | The preamble notes "All of products revenue is attributable to the Connectivity segment," implying AI is entirely services, but no explicit AI products/services table line is shown |\n| **Grok-specific standalone revenue** | Never isolated; always bundled with X subscriptions |\n| **Revenue by individual contract or customer** | Not disclosed |\n\n## Summary\n\nThe AI segment is disclosed at **two levels of revenue granularity in the financial tables**: Advertising and AI Solutions & Infrastructure. A **third qualitative level** (subscriptions, data licensing, API access) is described in the revenue recognition policy but is **not quantified in the tables**. The MD&A partially bridges this gap by disclosing YoY change amounts for subscriptions and data licensing (but not API access), and only for the most recent annual and quarterly comparisons.',
